<br>
Basically, it was on recent events here in the US and abroad.<br>
I logged off EQ only to see reports of ANTI-French slogans and graffiti on the news.  Not exactly what I'm itching to see.<br>
<br>
I just thought I'd share a couple things with you guys and maybe put my mind at ease. I know we have some people from EF that are in the US military and for that I say thankyou.  I support you guys where ever your are or may be going.  I dont' want to get into an arguement about whether our leaders are doing the right thing. I just wanted to bring attention to our own attitudes.  <br>
<br>
Some but not many of you know that I was actually married in France a couple years ago.   My (was to be wife) and I were both Americans (both in college) and thought this would be a wonderful way to start off our lives together.  It is a beautiful country with very nice people, but has a reputation of rudeness.  I have to say New York city doesn't have a reputation for helpful people either. I just think you will find all sorts of people where ever you go.    I'm saying all this just in hopes of asking you guys to see that we are in need of more than our own safety and well being.   We need the support of these other nations.  They are not our enemies.<br>
<br>
    The first time I was over to Europe I was actually travelling through Hungary and that region.   It was when we were sending bombing raids down to Yugoslavia.  I remember staying with a hungarian couple eating dinner and you could hear the NATO planes flying over head from the base in Germany to their targets about 150 miles to the south of where I was.  There were &quot; 'Nazi sign' = Nato&quot; graffittied on billboards.  I remember getting really nervous walking past a crowd of protesters. <br>
        Shortly there after when bush was elected and we backed out of the green house gas emissions treaty.  This brought more anti american political feelings through out the world.   I remember reading &quot;F_ _ _  Bush&quot; and other such slogans on bathroom walls in Ireland.  <br>
      I like to think of myself as someone who values other cultures and other perspectives.  I enjoy talking to people about ideas, and especially foreigners and their first impressions of the US.<br>
This is an amazing country we live it. Built buy all nationalities.<br>
I just  hope to soften any any anti-world ideas that some of you might have.   Wasn't sure what else to say...Please don't encourage vindictave and hateful acts against other nationalities.   always a pleasure <br>
cheers,<br>
John<br>
